# Customer Churn MLOps Pipeline

# Project Overview
This project implements an end-to-end MLOps pipeline for customer churn prediction. The main goal is to design a system that can handle data ingestion, preprocessing, model training, deployment, and monitoring in a structured and reproducible way.

The system predicts whether a customer is likely to churn based on input features. A lightweight Streamlit frontend is also included to allow interactive user predictions. SQLite is used as a lightweight relational database to store historical and incoming customer data.

# Pipeline Structure
The pipeline consists of the following components:

1. Data Ingestion  
Historical customer data is first stored in a lightweight SQLite database. New incoming customer data is also stored separately to simulate live data updates. The ingestion pipeline merges new records into the historical dataset and logs each update for monitoring and reproducibility.

2. Preprocessing  
The pipeline reads customer data from the SQLite database, then performs preprocessing by handling missing values, converting data types, and encoding categorical variables. Feature engineering is also applied where necessary.

3. Model Training  
A machine learning model is trained using the processed dataset. The trained model is saved as an artifact for reuse.

4. Deployment  
A FastAPI application is used to serve the trained model. The API accepts input data and returns predictions.

5. Monitoring  
Prediction logs are stored to track system behavior. Data ingestion is also logged to monitor data updates over time.

# Project Structure
customer-churn-mlops
├── app/            # FastAPI application
├── src/            # pipeline scripts (ingestion, preprocessing, training)
├── data/           # CSV files and SQLite database
│   ├── database.db # SQLite database for customer data
├── artifacts/      # model, logs, metrics
├── frontend.py     # Streamlit frontend
├── Dockerfile      # container setup

# How to Run (without Docker)
Step 1: Install dependencies  
pip install -r requirements.txt  

Step 2: Initialize the SQLite database  
python src/init_db.py  

Step 3: Run the ingestion pipeline  
python src/ingestion.py  

Step 4: Run preprocessing  
python src/preprocessing.py  

Step 5: Train the model  
python src/train.py  

Step 6: Run the API  
uvicorn app.main:app --reload  

Step 7: Open browser  
http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs  

Step 8: Run Streamlit frontend  
streamlit run frontend.py  

Step 9: Frontend can be accessed locally via:  
http://localhost:8501

# How to Run with Docker
Step 1: Build Docker image  
docker build -t churn-app .  

Step 2: Run container  
docker run -p 8000:8000 churn-app  

Step 3: Open  
http://localhost:8000/docs  

